{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "ChapmanMechanism",
        "description": "Stratospheric Chapman mechanism for ozone production and destruction (Seinfeld & Pandis 2006 Ch. 5, §5.2, Eqs. 5.1-5.17). Two-state ODE on atomic oxygen O and ozone O3 driven by the four canonical Chapman reactions: O2 photolysis (j_O2), three-body recombination O + O2 + M → O3 + M (k2 with power-law T-dependence (T_ref/T)^2.4), O3 photolysis (j_O3), and the O + O3 → 2 O2 odd-oxygen sink (k4 with Arrhenius temperature dependence). Odd oxygen Ox = O + O3 is *not* exactly conserved — the Chapman cycle has a net Ox source (2·j_O2·O2·M from O2 photolysis) balanced against an Ox sink (2·k4·O·O3 from the O+O3 reaction) — but on short timescales (≲ 10 s under default mid-stratosphere conditions) the net change is small (~4e-5 relative drift) and the upstream test treats it as quasi-conserved at rtol=1e-4. Migrated from GasChem.jl@8c12c048 src/StratosphericChemistry.jl:51 (`ChapmanMechanism` @component). Rate coefficients carry SI units throughout, converted from Seinfeld & Pandis CGS values via cm^6/molec^2/s × 1e-12 → m^6/s for the 3-body k2 and cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → m^3/s for the bimolecular k4.",
        "tags": [
            "gaschem",
            "stratospheric",
            "chapman",
            "ozone",
            "photochemistry",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "ode"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-12T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "GasChem.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-w9h2)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H. and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, John Wiley & Sons, Hoboken, NJ. Chapter 5 (Chemistry of the Stratosphere), §5.2 (Chapman Mechanism), pp. 138-149, Eqs. 5.1-5.17."
            },
            {
                "citation": "Brasseur, G. P. and Solomon, S. (2005). Aeronomy of the Middle Atmosphere, 3rd revised and enlarged edition, Springer, Dordrecht. §5.2 (Pure Oxygen Stratosphere). Supporting reference for the Chapman cycle's odd-oxygen budget and the timescale separation between fast O ↔ O3 cycling and slow Ox source-sink chemistry."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "ChapmanMechanism": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/StratosphericChemistry.jl:51\n\nUpstream `ChapmanMechanism` is an MTK `@component` declaring four `@constants` (the 3-body Chapman pre-factor `k2_A` = 6.0e-46 m^6/s for O+O2+M→O3+M, the bimolecular `k4_A` = 8.0e-18 m^3/s for O+O3→2O2, the Arrhenius temperature scale `C_k4` = -2060.0 K for k4, and the reference temperature `T_ref` = 300.0 K for the power-law k2), five `@parameters` (`j_O2` = 1e-10 s^-1 O2 photolysis rate, `j_O3` = 1e-3 s^-1 O3 photolysis rate, `T` = 227.0 K mid-stratosphere reference temperature ~30 km altitude, `M` = 3.0e23 m^-3 air number density 3e17 molec/cm^3 × 1e6, `O2_mix` = 0.21 dimensionless O2 mixing ratio in air), three time-indexed `@variables` (`O(t)` = 1.0e13 m^-3 atomic oxygen default 1e7 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 from S&P Page 145, `O3(t)` = 3.0e18 m^-3 ozone default 3e12 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 from S&P Page 145, and `Ox(t)` the algebraic odd-oxygen family sum), and three equations (two ODEs and one algebraic constraint). Identical structure preserved here. Upstream structural test (test/StratosphericChemistry_test.jl 'Chapman Mechanism Structure', lines 38-49) asserts `length(equations(sys)) == 3` and that O(t), O3(t), and Ox(t) appear in `unknowns(sys)` — matched here by the three entries in `equations` and the O/O3/Ox state declarations in `variables`.\n\nThe four upstream `@constants` (k2_A, k4_A, C_k4, T_ref) are encoded here as `type: parameter` with the upstream values as `default`, matching the convention used by the sibling stratospheric migrations in this rig (hox_cycle.esm encodes its eight upstream `@constants` the same way; clox_cycle.esm encodes its many `@constants` the same way; this is the rig-wide convention for `@constants` migration). The five upstream `@parameters` (j_O2, j_O3, T, M, O2_mix) are also `type: parameter` with their upstream defaults — they were already MTK parameters upstream, so the parameter-vs-constant distinction collapses at the `.esm` schema level. A downstream consumer that wants to override the Chapman rate coefficients (e.g. to test sensitivity to the Table B.1/B.2 rate-coefficient updates between S&P 2006 and JPL 2019) reads them from `parameter_overrides` exactly as it would override T, M, or j_O2.\n\nUpstream rate-coefficient helper bindings (`k2 = k2_A * (T_ref / T)^2.4` and `k4 = k4_A * exp(C_k4 / T)`) and the O2 binding (`O2 = O2_mix * M`) are local Julia bindings expanded into the equation right-hand-sides — they are not user-visible MTK state variables (no `@variables k2`, `@variables k4`, `@variables O2`) so the upstream `unknowns(sys)` returns exactly O, O3, Ox after `mtkcompile`. The migrated `.esm` preserves this by inlining the three sub-expressions directly into each reaction-flux term on the right-hand sides — bit-equivalent to writing the equations with the helper bindings, and matches the `length(unknowns(sys)) == 3` invariant the upstream structural test enforces.\n\nOdd-oxygen (Ox) is *not* exactly conserved by construction in the Chapman cycle — sum of the two ODE right-hand-sides gives `D(O) + D(O3) = 2·j_O2·O2·M - 2·k4·O·O3` (the k2 three-body term and the j_O3 photolysis term cancel exactly because they shuttle O ↔ O3 within the family; only the O2 photolysis source and the O+O3 → 2·O2 sink remain). The algebraic equation `Ox ~ O + O3` simply names the family sum for downstream observers — its value drifts at a rate `D(Ox) = 2·j_O2·O2·M - 2·k4·O·O3` set by the small Chapman source-sink imbalance. Under default conditions (j_O2 = 1e-10, O2 = O2_mix·M = 6.3e22, k4·O3 ≈ 2.8e-3 1/s) the radical-equilibrium O ≈ 1.36e14 m^-3 gives a source ≈ 1.26e13 m^-3/s and a sink ≈ 7.5e11 m^-3/s — a net Ox growth of ~1.18e13 m^-3/s, or ~4e-6 relative per second. On the 10-second window of the upstream 'Odd Oxygen Conservation (Chapman)' test (StratosphericChemistry_test.jl:248-264) this gives ~4e-5 absolute drift relative to the initial 3.00001e18 m^-3 Ox value — within the upstream `rtol = 1e-4` tolerance. The migrated `odd_oxygen_quasi_conservation_short` test below pins the actual Ox trajectory (rather than just asserting conservation) so any structural break in the migration shows up as a wrong-magnitude drift, not just a tolerance failure.\n\nFast radical equilibrium: under default conditions the O atom has a very short lifetime (lifetime ≈ 1 / (k2·O2·M + k4·O3) ≈ 1 / (22.1 + 2.8e-3) ≈ 0.045 s, dominated by the k2·O2·M three-body sink with k2 = k2_A·(300/227)^2.4 ≈ 1.17e-45 m^6/s, O2·M = O2_mix·M^2 = 0.21·9e46 = 1.89e46). O reaches quasi-equilibrium with O3 by t ≈ 0.5 s at a steady-state value O_eq ≈ (2·j_O2·O2·M + j_O3·O3) / (k2·O2·M + k4·O3) ≈ (1.26e13 + 3e15) / 22.1 ≈ 1.36e14 m^-3 (the 3e15 j_O3·O3 channel dominates the source). After that fast settling, O follows the much slower Ox evolution adiabatically (O ≈ O3 · j_O3 / (k2·O2·M + k4·O3) ∝ O3 at fixed environment, S&P Eq. 5.7). The 'default_short_term_10s' test pins the early-time transient up to t = 10 s where O has long since reached its radical equilibrium; 'default_long_term_1day' pins the slow Ox drift over 24 hours.\n\nTemperature dependence: k2 has a power-law T-dependence (T_ref/T)^2.4 (Table B.2 of S&P), unique among the stratospheric rate coefficients in this rig — sibling cycles use Arrhenius forms exclusively. The 'cold_temperature_perturbation' (T = 200 K) and 'warm_temperature_perturbation' (T = 270 K) tests exercise the joint k2/k4 temperature response: at 200 K, k2 = 1.6e-45 (2× faster) while k4 = 8e-18·exp(-10.3) = 2.7e-22 (14× slower than at 227 K), so O accumulates less (1.02e14 vs 1.36e14 default at 1 hour) because the dominant k2 sink is faster. At 270 K, k2 = 7.6e-46 (0.65× slower) and k4 = 8e-18·exp(-7.63) = 3.9e-21 (4.3× faster), so O accumulates more (2.06e14) due to slower k2 sink, but Ox depletes faster due to faster k4·O·O3 odd-oxygen loss.\n\nDensity dependence: M scales O+O2+M three-body production as M^2 (the explicit M factor times the implicit O2 = O2_mix·M factor) and the O2 photolysis source as M (via O2 = O2_mix·M). At higher M (denser, lower altitudes), the M^2 sink for O dominates the M source — O is pushed to a very low steady state (1.4e11 at M=1e25, vs 1.36e14 at M=3e23). At lower M (thinner, higher altitudes), the M^2 sink weakens faster than the source — O accumulates to ~8.6e16 at M=1e22, but Ox actually *decreases* over time because the k4·O·O3 sink becomes proportionally stronger relative to the weakened 2·j_O2·O2_mix·M production. The 'dense_M_perturbation' (M = 1e25) and 'thin_M_perturbation' (M = 1e22) tests pin both regimes.\n\nUnit balance (verified): each flux term has units consistent with d[X]/dt for X in m^-3. The k2 three-body term `k2 · O · O2 · M = (m^6/s) · (m^-3) · (m^-3) · (m^-3) = m^-3/s` ✓. The k4 bimolecular term `k4 · O · O3 = (m^3/s) · (m^-3) · (m^-3) = m^-3/s` ✓. The photolysis terms `j_O2 · O2_mix · M = (1/s) · (1) · (m^-3) = m^-3/s` and `j_O3 · O3 = (1/s) · (m^-3) = m^-3/s` ✓. The (T_ref/T)^2.4 factor is dimensionless because both are in K. The exp(C_k4/T) factor is dimensionless because C_k4 is in K and T is in K. The migrated `.esm` preserves the upstream units verbatim — k2_A in m^6/s, k4_A in m^3/s, C_k4 and T_ref in K, j_O2 and j_O3 in 1/s, T in K, M and O and O3 and Ox in m^-3, O2_mix dimensionless. SI throughout; no CGS↔SI conversion at parse or runtime.\n\nObservability classification: this is an active-ODE system (two state derivatives D(O), D(O3) plus one algebraic Ox constraint), like sibling stratospheric components. Test scenarios sample at non-zero times (t = 0.1, 1.0, 5.0, 10.0, 60.0, 600.0, 1800.0, 3600.0, 21600.0, 86400.0 s across the suite) to exercise both the fast O radical-equilibrium transient (t ≲ 1 s) and the slow Ox source/sink drift (t ≳ 1 hour). The fast-vs-slow timescale separation is the headline behavior the suite captures.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): two-state stiff ODE with widely separated timescales (O equilibrium lifetime ~0.045 s under default conditions, Ox drift timescale ~hours-to-days). The expected values pinned below are LSODA references from the canonical ESS Python runner (`earthsci_toolkit.simulation.simulate(rtol=1e-10, atol=1e-12, cse=False)` — the same settings the inline-test driver uses), so the cross-integrator drift between reference and gate is zero by construction. Model-level rel=1e-6 matches the spec §6.6.4 default and accommodates accumulated round-off across the long 86400 s window of the 'default_long_term_1day' test (~7e-11 ULP × 86400 / 0.045 s steps ≈ 1.3e-4 cumulative, but bounded by the integrator's adaptive step control). On `initial_conditions_t0` the per-test tolerance is tightened to rel=1e-10 / abs=1e-14 because at t=0 there is no integration drift — only parser→Float64 conversion and the first-step identity evaluation of the initial state. On `zero_photolysis_radical_decay` the assertions on O reaching numerical zero use abs=1e-10 to accommodate the floating-point underflow of a negative-exponential decay below the atol=1e-12 integrator floor.\n\nUpstream test reproduction: the upstream structural test ('Chapman Mechanism Structure', `length(equations(sys)) == 3` with O/O3/Ox state names, lines 38-49) is reproduced by the test-level shape of the `variables` and `equations` blocks. The upstream integration test ('Chapman Mechanism Integration', lines 136-150: 1-day default-IC solve with `abstol=1e-8, reltol=1e-8` asserting `sol.retcode == ReturnCode.Success` and positivity on O and O3) is reproduced and extended by 'default_long_term_1day', which pins not just positivity but the actual O, O3, Ox values at four times across the 24-hour window. The upstream conservation test ('Odd Oxygen Conservation (Chapman)', lines 248-264: 10-second default-IC solve with `abstol=1e-12, reltol=1e-12` asserting `isapprox(Ox_initial, Ox_final, rtol=1e-4)`) is reproduced by `odd_oxygen_quasi_conservation_short`, which pins the actual Ox trajectory at five times in [0, 10] s — both the quasi-conservation bound *and* the magnitude of the slow drift. The upstream zero-photolysis test ('Zero Photolysis Rates', lines 502-523: 1-hour solve with `j_O2=0, j_O3=0` asserting `O[end] < O[1]`) is reproduced and tightened by `zero_photolysis_radical_decay`, which pins O collapsing to numerical zero (~3e-23 m^-3 by t=60 s) and O3 holding at the post-collapse value 3.00001e18 m^-3. The upstream positivity-preservation test ('Positivity Preservation', lines 228-242) is implicitly covered by `default_short_term_10s` and `default_long_term_1day` which pin strictly-positive values throughout. Parameter-sweep coverage (T, M, j_O3, initial conditions) goes beyond the upstream test suite — the upstream 'Chapman Steady-State [O]/[O3] Ratio' test (lines 365-401) uses j_O3=4e-4 to anchor Eq. 5.7's order-of-magnitude prediction with rtol=0.1; the migrated `reduced_jO3_perturbation` test exercises the same parameter override at the canonical default M but at the tighter rel=1e-6 quantitative level rather than the upstream's order-of-magnitude check."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-6
            },
            "variables": {
                "k2_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^6/s",
                    "default": 6.0e-46,
                    "description": "Pre-factor for the O + O2 + M → O3 + M three-body recombination rate coefficient k2 = k2_A · (T_ref/T)^2.4 (S&P Table B.2; 6e-34 cm^6/molec^2/s × 1e-12 → m^6/s)."
                },
                "k4_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/s",
                    "default": 8.0e-18,
                    "description": "Pre-factor for the O + O3 → 2 O2 bimolecular rate coefficient k4 = k4_A · exp(C_k4/T) (S&P Table B.1; 8e-12 cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → m^3/s)."
                },
                "C_k4": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": -2060.0,
                    "description": "Arrhenius activation temperature for O + O3 → 2 O2 (S&P Table B.1)."
                },
                "T_ref": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Reference temperature for the k2 power-law T-dependence (S&P Table B.2). The k2 coefficient is fit as 6e-34 · (T/300)^-2.4 in CGS, equivalent to k2_A · (T_ref/T)^2.4 in SI."
                },
                "j_O2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "default": 1.0e-10,
                    "description": "O2 photolysis rate constant (S&P Page 142, S-R band photolysis at ~30 km mid-stratosphere)."
                },
                "j_O3": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "default": 1.0e-3,
                    "description": "O3 photolysis rate constant (S&P Page 142, Hartley band photolysis at ~30 km mid-stratosphere)."
                },
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 227.0,
                    "description": "Local temperature for the k2 and k4 rate-coefficient evaluations (S&P Page 145 mid-stratosphere reference, ~30 km)."
                },
                "M": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 3.0e23,
                    "description": "Air number density (3e17 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → m^-3; S&P Page 145 mid-stratosphere reference, ~30 km). Acts as the three-body collider in k2·O·O2·M and as the source of background O2 via O2 = O2_mix · M."
                },
                "O2_mix": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 0.21,
                    "description": "O2 mixing ratio in air (dimensionless). Combined with M to give O2 number density: O2 = O2_mix · M. Background O2 is assumed at the standard atmospheric mixing ratio throughout the stratosphere (S&P Page 142)."
                },
                "O": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e13,
                    "description": "Atomic oxygen O(3P) number density (1e7 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → m^-3; S&P Page 145 stratospheric reference). State variable: D(O) = 2·j_O2·O2_mix·M - k2_A·(T_ref/T)^2.4·O·O2_mix·M^2 + j_O3·O3 - k4_A·exp(C_k4/T)·O·O3. Has a very short lifetime (~0.045 s under default conditions) and rapidly reaches a quasi-equilibrium with O3 governed by S&P Eq. 5.7."
                },
                "O3": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 3.0e18,
                    "description": "Ozone number density (3e12 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → m^-3; S&P Page 145 stratospheric reference). State variable: D(O3) = k2_A·(T_ref/T)^2.4·O·O2_mix·M^2 - j_O3·O3 - k4_A·exp(C_k4/T)·O·O3. The O3 timescale is set by the slow Chapman source/sink imbalance (D(Ox) ≈ 2·j_O2·O2·M - 2·k4·O·O3) — much slower than the fast O ↔ O3 cycling within the family."
                },
                "Ox": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "description": "Odd-oxygen family: algebraic sum Ox ~ O + O3 (S&P §5.2). Not exactly conserved — Chapman has a net Ox source (2·j_O2·O2·M, O2 photolysis adds two O atoms per O2) balanced against an Ox sink (2·k4·O·O3, the O+O3 → 2 O2 reaction removes one O and one O3 per encounter). On short timescales (≲ 10 s under default conditions) the relative drift is ~4e-5; on long timescales (hours-to-days) Ox approaches a steady state set by the j_O2/k4 ratio."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["O"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    2.0,
                                    "j_O2",
                                    "O2_mix",
                                    "M"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    -1.0,
                                    "k2_A",
                                    {"op": "^", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["T_ref", "T"]}, 2.4]},
                                    "O",
                                    "O2_mix",
                                    "M",
                                    "M"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "j_O3",
                                    "O3"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    -1.0,
                                    "k4_A",
                                    {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_k4", "T"]}]},
                                    "O",
                                    "O3"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["O3"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "k2_A",
                                    {"op": "^", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["T_ref", "T"]}, 2.4]},
                                    "O",
                                    "O2_mix",
                                    "M",
                                    "M"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    -1.0,
                                    "j_O3",
                                    "O3"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    -1.0,
                                    "k4_A",
                                    {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_k4", "T"]}]},
                                    "O",
